Introduction
Meson production is one of the most significant phenomena in hadronic interactions, playing a crucial role in fields such as astrophysics, cosmic ray physics, and accelerator technology. In this study, we provide differential data on meson production in the federal collision of relativistic protons with tantalum (reaction, π+). These experiments were carried out at the CYCLONE laboratory in JINR-Dubna.

Experimental Setup
The experimental setup used in our experiment includes:
- Two scintillation detectors, S1 and S2;
- Three scintillation detectors;
- An improved collimator;
- A target made of 0.1 mm thick tantalum foil;
- A detection system consisting of four scintillation detectors, T1-T4.

